Let’s be honest – who here doesn’t love sushi? I could eat it daily although I don’t need or want that much rice every week. Which is why this low-carb, 100% plant-based rainbow cucumber sushi is the perfect compromise! I’ve shared options similar in my story for years but this is awesome! By @alphafoodie

This rainbow cucumber sushi is not only 100% plant-based , but can be made in under 15 minutes and perfect for a healthy, delicious low-carb lunch or snack served alongside a delicious vegan avocado dip!

Ingredients:

-1/2 banana
-1/2 cup frozen blueberries
-1 tbsp honey
-1 tsp baking powder
-pinch of salt
-1/4 cup dairy free milk

Steps:
-blend ingredients together
-add to an oven safe container
-air fry at 350F for 10 minutes (or bake in the oven for ~20)
-enjoy!
-tag me if you try it 😋

Egg White Breakfast Cups (Under 50 Calories) 🍳 
By: @buzzfeedtasty 
-
Ingredients
(for 6 servings)
2 cups spinach, 14 calories (60 g)
1 roma tomato, 11 calories
2 cups egg white, 250 calories (480 mL)
salt, to taste, 0 calories
½ teaspoon pepper, 0 calories
-
Preparation
Preheat the oven to 350˚F (180˚C).
Lightly grease a muffin tin.
Then divide equally the spinach across 6 cups.
Dice the tomato, then fill the cups with the tomato and egg whites.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until the whites have set.
Serve hot.
Enjoy! 
 
#eggs #egg #eggwhite #eggwhites #protein #mealprep #foodprep

node.text:
Follow @laura_lambe to learn how to transform your physique and still eat your favourite foods. 
 
Skewerless Chicken Kabobs 🔥

All the flavors of our FAVORITE chicken kabobs without a grill!…By @cleanfoodcrush

This makes for an awesome meal year-round, and comes together pretty quickly!

Lots of flavors, lots of veggies...this one is SO GOOD!

Double up the recipe, then you'll have lunch ready for the next few days ahead! Stays great in the fridge for 3 days.

I served brown rice alongside, but I think cauliflower rice or quinoa would both be wonderful too!

6 servings

Ingredients
2 lbs chicken breast & thighs (skinless boneless), cut into 3/4-inch cubes
2 Tbsps olive oil or avocado oil, divided
sea salt and ground pepper, to taste
2 large bell peppers, cut into 3/4-inch pieces (red & yellow)
2 medium zucchini, cut into 1/2-inch slices
1 large red onion, cut into wedges
1/2 pound medium fresh mushrooms, halved
1 cup ripe cherry tomatoes
3 cloves fresh garlic, minced 
1 Tbsp Italian seasoning
curly parsley, to garnish

Instructions:

Season your chicken with sea salt and pepper on all sides.

Heat half of your oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add in the chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden-brown and cooked through, 10-12 minutes. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl add all of your prepped veggies (besides tomatoes), garlic, Italian seasoning, and season with a pinch of sea salt and pepper. Stir to coat well.

Once the chicken is done and set aside, and preheat the remaining oil in the same skillet again over high heat.

Add seasoned veggies and cook for 4-5 minutes, or until tender-crisp.

Return the chicken back into your skillet together with the cherry tomatoes and toss to heat everything up.

Sprinkle with fresh chopped parsley and serve with brown rice or quinoa.

Enjoy!
 
#chicken #grilling #grill #grilledchicken

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by @eatinghealthytoday on August 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, drink and text that says 'CAN'T FIND TIME FOR THE GYM BUT SPENDS 2 HOURS ON SOCIAL MEDIA EVERY DAY @BODYSMARTFITNESS BUT THAT'S NONE OF MY BUSINESS'.

node.text:
👉 Follow @bodysmartfitness the best fitness, nutrition and mindset tips (and the memes!) 
   
Follow 👉  @bodysmartfitness⁣⁣   
 
⌚ "I haven't got time" is just another form of saying "This is not important enough to me."⁣ 
⁣ 
👉 Sorry to be blunt about this one but one of our biggest modern epidemics is the time we haemorrhage on social media.⁣ 
⁣ 
📲 First of all let us at @bodysmartfitness⁣⁣  hold our hands up and say we are all guilty when it comes to spending a ridiculous amount of hours online. ⁣ 
⁣ 
👉 So with that confession out of the way, one thing I would say is the time we personally spend online is our livelihood. Social media is our shop window and the way we help people to get inspired to move in a way they love, eat the foods they love guilt-free and develop a strong mindset to create lifelong change. We do that by sharing our expertise over on the @bodysmartfitness Instagram account and other awesome food and fitness accounts like this one. 
⁣ 
💪 So if you also run an online business I completely understand the time and commitment needed to be online. I hope, like we have done, that you've found a balance and crafted non-negotiable time into your daily routine to factor in the most important stuff like exercise, fresh air, relaxation, reflection and visualisation along with working online.⁣ 
⁣ 
⏱ If not, and you're reading this as someone who currently doesn't train but does leech hours scrolling endlessly through the quagmire of content on all social platforms, please do have a word with yourself. Check your device and see how many average hours a day you spend on different platforms.⁣ 
⁣ 
👩‍🏫 According to Statista.com, smartphone use increased during the pandemic across the world by a huge 70%!!! 
 
It's madness. What are we achieving by staring into our phones? Stop kidding yourself. Stop making excuses. If you're ready to make a change for the better and live your life to the full, at @bodysmartfitness we're ready to help.⁣ 
⁣  
Follow 👉  @bodysmartfitness⁣⁣   
Follow 👉  @bodysmartfitness⁣⁣   
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness⁣⁣   
⁣ 
#meme #fitnessmeme #fitnesshumour #diethumour #kermitmeme #socialmedia
